Java code requirement: You are given a list of integers. Write a function nextSmallest() that returns the 2nd smallest element of the list. Return null if there is no such element. nextSmallest(Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)) == Optional[2], nextSmallest(Arrays.asList(5, 1, 4, 3, 2)) == Optional[2], nextSmallest(Arrays.asList()) == Optional.empty, nextSmallest(Arrays.asList(1, 1)) == Optional.empty. student code: import java.util.*;
class Solution {
    public Optional<Integer> nextSmallest(List<Integer> lst) {
        Collections.sort(lst);
        if (lst.size() < 2) {
            return Optional.empty();
        }
        return Optional.of(lst.get(1));
    }
}
